# EXStreamTV ‚Äî Confluence & Wiki Publishing

Full lessons: **LL-031‚ÄìLL-036** in `docs/LESSONS_LEARNED.md` ¬∑ dual-target workflow: `.cursor/rules/exstreamtv-documentation-parity.mdc`

## RULE DOC-01 ‚Äî Confluence: Storage REST vs ADF MCP

- **Rendered Markdown + visible diagrams**: use **Confluence REST** + `scripts/confluence_markdown_storage.py`. **`publish_confluence_wiki_tree.py`** POSTs each Mermaid block to **[Kroki](https://kroki.io)**, uploads returned **SVG** as a page attachment, and references it with **`ri:attachment`** (no Mermaid marketplace app required). `CONFLUENCE_SKIP_KROKI=1` falls back to the **code** macro (`language=mermaid`) only.
- **`publish_confluence_mirror.py`** (single page) still uses the code macro for Mermaid unless extended.
- **Atlassian MCP** `createConfluencePage`: body must be **ADF JSON** ‚Äî not a substitute for the storage + Kroki path above.

## RULE DOC-02 ‚Äî uv: Invoke PEP 723 Scripts by Path

- Run: `uv run scripts/publish_confluence_wiki_tree.py` and `uv run scripts/publish_confluence_mirror.py` (script path as argument to `uv run`).
- Do **not** use `uv run python scripts/...` for those files if they declare `# /// script` dependencies ‚Äî `markdown` may be missing (LL-032).

## RULE DOC-03 ‚Äî Confluence: Avoid Title Collisions

- Titles must be **unique within the space**.
- Root landing **`EXStreamTV`** + wiki file `EXStreamTV.md`: use **`confluence_wiki_child_title()`** from `wiki_sidebar_order.py` (child ‚Üí **EXStreamTV Wiki**).

## RULE DOC-04 ‚Äî Wiki Sidebar & Legacy Titles

- Sidebar order: single source **`SIDBAR_STEMS`** in `scripts/wiki_sidebar_order.py` (used by mirror builders and wiki tree publisher).
- Reusing pages from an old **‚ÄúMirror ‚Äî ‚Ä¶‚Äù** tree: `publish_confluence_wiki_tree.py` matches legacy titles and renames on update ‚Äî do not reintroduce the **Mirror ‚Äî** prefix for new publishes.

## RULE DOC-05 ‚Äî Confluence REST: No Default `Content-Type: application/json` on Multipart-Capable Clients

- **`POST ‚Ä¶/wiki/rest/api/content/{id}/child/attachment`** requires **`multipart/form-data`** (file field `file`).  
- **Never** set **`Content-Type: application/json`** on the **`httpx.Client`** default headers used for both JSON API calls **and** file uploads ‚Äî Confluence returns **415** for every attachment (Kroki **mermaid-*.svg**, wiki screenshots, etc.).  
- **Correct pattern:** default headers = **`Accept: application/json`** only; use **`json=‚Ä¶`** on `post`/`put` for JSON (httpx sets JSON content type per request); use **`files=‚Ä¶`** for attachments (httpx sets multipart + boundary).  
- **Lesson:** LL-034.

## RULE DOC-06 ‚Äî Confluence: Reuse Root Page or Set `CONFLUENCE_ROOT_PAGE_ID`

- A **second** publish without **`CONFLUENCE_ROOT_PAGE_ID`** must **not** `POST` another page with the same root title ‚Äî Confluence returns **400** (duplicate title in space).
- **`publish_confluence_wiki_tree.py`** reuses an existing root by **title lookup** in the space when the env var is unset; you may still set **`CONFLUENCE_ROOT_PAGE_ID`** explicitly.
- **Lesson:** LL-035.
